[
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1053_549_218",
    "text": "I slowly got up, tired and shaky.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_106_79_5",
    "text": "It's like no matter what happens, I'm always going to be anxious about having a serious disease.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_117_200_32",
    "text": "I could feel myself on the edge of a panic attack, so I just focused on getting dressed and then fiddled with some origami I'd been working on until I could calm down some.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1190_12_0",
    "text": "Sometimes when I wake up particularly anxious I'll have three loose movements within an hour.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1194_70_1",
    "text": "like when im anxious i feel like im losing mind or going crazy",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1245_192_1",
    "text": "When I am stressed and anxious I feel like I have to do something productive and finish the task so that I feel I have accomplished something--anything--then that sets me up to keep completing tasks.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1265_395_5",
    "text": "And then today I felt less down but now agitated and irritable.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1269_0_11",
    "text": "Like I was experiencing elevated heartrate/feeling like it was racing, feeling like I couldn't catch my breath, crying for no reason, being jumpy/paranoid, etc.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1269_0_4",
    "text": "I tried doing things that usually help calm me but it wasn't helping.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1269_990_0",
    "text": "I tend to experience brain fog more if my depression or anxiety has been worse recently.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1271_706_3",
    "text": "After about five night of listening I find I have much less anxiety and am more relaxed.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1283_37_5",
    "text": "Having a consistent sleep pattern was important, and even felt like if I exercised too much, or did anything that might through the pattern off (like a nap), the attacks were somehow worse.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1325_15_6",
    "text": "I could feel my chest getting tense.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1330_3_5",
    "text": "The last time this happened I attempted to relax through it but due to the difficulty of breathing subtly as I was beforehand it lessened my relaxation and left me feeling quite awake.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_134_406_5",
    "text": "Anxiety kind of forces me to multitask and complete things fully and quickly.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1404_777_3",
    "text": "Why am I always tired and stressed?",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1418_1432_9",
    "text": "This question is probably pretty ridiculous, but I just feel like an anxious mess when using phones (talking over people, awkward silences, so forth) so maybe I'm overanalysing, but I don't know what I'm doing so I thought I may as well ask.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1514_41_272",
    "text": "I was getting increasingly fatigued, but I was far too tense to sleep for many reasons.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1528_4_36",
    "text": "After some seconds I calmed down, and the panic faded a bit.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1551_249_3",
    "text": "But I feel impatient, Im starting to feel like Ive missed out on a lot in the past 5 years because of things that werent in my control and its consuming my mind.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1597_656_3",
    "text": "No cigarette in 6 hours and I have restless legs, etc.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1625_62_0",
    "text": "Works great for me situationally, when anxiety is through the roof.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1633_901_0",
    "text": "well I agree with you, there's a lot of other factors I did not state here, even I don't know what makes me feel anxious and troubles me continuously that is what I want to figure out, plus idk why from the past few months I feel very emotional at minor inconveniences and used to be a foodie and have now lost apettite and many other things likethis.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1764_74_0",
    "text": "I'm always anxious about people being mad at me.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1805_1381_5",
    "text": "I sleep until I feel tired from sleeping too much.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1900_882_46",
    "text": "I was becoming agitated and more pissed off than afraid at this point.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_1933_127_1",
    "text": "I've been very stressed because I'm trying to do too many things with too little time, so I may have freaked out a little more than necessary.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2006_3_1",
    "text": "I feel better now that I'm off, not AS anxious.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2035_4_1",
    "text": "My biggest trigger to smoke is getting angry or anxious.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2070_41_10",
    "text": "My body is tense and I feel hopeless and angry at the same time.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2070_41_8",
    "text": "Now I am generally very anxious and agitated.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_212_349_4",
    "text": "When I vented for 1 hour non stop I felt energetic, clear minded, powerful, highly disciplined, happy and most importantly; no longer anxious or in despair but powerful and capable.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2135_5_19",
    "text": "I have trouble calming down at night and falling asleep).",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2139_274_0",
    "text": "I would have weeks of depression and then suddenly feel good and talk fast, agitation, not sleeping, productive, impulsiveness etc then i would go right back down to depression.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2139_298_4",
    "text": "When people talk to me or make noise I start to feel overwhelmed and agitated.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2139_80_5",
    "text": "Meanwhile the depressive episodes have me hanging on for dear life, the hypomania causes restlessness and because I am extremely self aware, I can feel my body being fidgety and see myself making bad decisions.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2184_234_2",
    "text": "I mostly grind when I'm sleeping but I do it when I get stressed and anxious too",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_220_1119_12",
    "text": "I have diagnosed depression and anxiety and one of my symptoms when I get seriously upset is that I can't sleep, which manifested into this.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_220_1368_21",
    "text": "I am incredibly anxious all the time.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2257_110_13",
    "text": "Anxiety and depression: Pretty sure, because I often am nervous when carrying out even the simplest tasks and interacting with others (even my family members), and I love my comfort zones like my bed and my room and I feel uneasy whenever I have to leave them.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2257_110_38",
    "text": "Sometimes I am really energized up and sometimes I'm lethargic.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2292_1472_5",
    "text": "I feel slightly sleepy.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2292_77_3",
    "text": "When I actually try to go to sleep, I get extremely anxious.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2326_303_2",
    "text": "i have been careful this whole time but im panicking now.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2338_1010_3",
    "text": "I've already got some things to help me out if and when the anxiety creeps up on me.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2338_1027_15",
    "text": "I get tired, my eyes go cross, my anxiety creeps back up on me.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2402_1046_7",
    "text": "I find it hard to calm down.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2402_1047_7",
    "text": "I find it hard to calm down.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2407_3_10",
    "text": "So not having him around really scares me simply because he makes me feel safer and less anxious and depressed.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2415_150_1",
    "text": "These days I am so overwhelmed and anxious that I don't breathe  for seconds.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2434_322_0",
    "text": "Well to say, my head twitches take place outside me playing games, and my tics have sort of gotten worse since I made the comment yesterday, so I dont really think my tics are linked specifically to anxiety anymore.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2434_474_0",
    "text": "Its sort of very hard for me to really fall asleep unless Im really tired, and my tics arent as bad since Im very low on energy.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2434_501_10",
    "text": "I cant even breathe sometimes with this stupid body shaking tic.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2439_91_1",
    "text": "I dont know how people co-sleep, Im too anxious.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2470_9_7",
    "text": "I too do not have the more obvious physical symptoms (restlessness ect.).",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2493_375_1",
    "text": "I really have to watch my state of mind and stress level.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
    "docid": "s_2625_640_7",
    "text": "I had some anxious moments, especially immediately post run when I started focusing on my heart beat, but I am calm now I feel just awesome.",
    "bdi_query": 11,
    "bdi_name": "Agitation",
    "majority": 1,
    "consensus": 0,
    "type": "disagreement",
    "source": "erisk2023"
  },
  {
    "symptom_id": 13,
